Body: Description: Within StealthAudit the custom report is completing without error but going into the report details shows no current data/activity.

@Mike Candon​ Not enough information provided. Very unlikely there is a custom report for SAM. We'll want to review the job in NEA that corresponds to the data they are receiving (an export of the entire job would be helpful since it's custom) as well as confirmation that SAM is picking up the data (via search).

This customer doesn't appear to be licensed for File System Reports in NEA, just File Activity in NAM. This may be left over from their 2020 demo?

 

In the FSAC System scan log I see the following errors:

ERROR TDCThread TDCThread.LoadSourceItf "No DC installed to handle source : FILESYSTEMACCESS"

ERROR TDCThread TDCThread.PrepareForTask "The 'FILESYSTEMACCESS' data collector has not been installed"

 

And then confirmed via the Support Portal "My Products Tool":

When we have potentially identified a feature or functionality issue, we should have the customer check their licensing for StealthAudit/NEA. 

 

It is also interesting that this Report is left over from a Demo from 2020.

What We've Learned Updated: I should have asked you to open StealthAudit (NEA) and navigate to "Help" > "About" and scroll down to the "File System" Licensed Features:

"File System"

"File System Actions"

"File System Reports"

+++++

1) It seems as though you may not be licensed for File System Reports in NEA but only File Activity in NAM. The report may be left over from a 2020 demo that was conducted for you?
